It was plauded by movie critics and hailed by activists for its championing of gay rights.

But marketing gurus have been forced to 'straight-wash' 2013 British film Pride - so that it appeals to a wide US audience.

The DVD cover of the movie, based on the campaign of a gay and lesbian activist group, has been altered - with any reference to the film's focal theme of homosexuality removed.

