Gay author Matt Cain also criticised the move, saying it went against the spirit of the film.

But Mr Cain, who is the former culture editor of Channel 4 News, said it will be a positive thing if it means more people buy the DVD and watch it.

Pride was not a huge hit at the box office, but was plauded by critics and has already won a series of awards.

In the US, it is nominated for a Golden Globe in the category of best comedy or musical film - with the ceremony taking place on Sunday.

