It was also named best film at the British Independent Film Awards in December.

Accepting the top award of the night, Pride director Matthew Warchus told the BBC: 'We're getting reports from up and down the country of audiences standing up and applauding. 

That doesn't really happen in British cinemas. It's just extraordinary. It's a real tribute to the source material.'

